term_definitions.items: Local cluster to capture episode details for the Northumbria Orthopaedic PROMS registry.
American Orthopaedic Foot and Ankle Society Score.
A specific date and/or time which may be explicitly defined in a template or at run-time.
Additional information required to capture local context or to align with other reference models/formalisms.
e.g. Local hospital departmental infomation or additional metadata to align with HL7 or CDISC equivalents.
Record any issues or factors that may impact on the overall assessment or score.
The total score for the four questions.
The patient reports mild or occasional pain.
The patient reports moderate or daily pain.
Q2 Activity limitations and support requirements
Patient-reported activity limitations and support requirements.
The patient reports no activity limitations and support requirements.
The patient reports mild or occasional activity limitations and support requirements.
The patient reports moderate or daily activity limitations and support requirements.
The patient reports severe activity limitations and support requirements.
Patient-reported maximum walking distance in blocks (1 block = 100-200 yards).
The patient reports a maximum walking distance of greater than 6 blocks.
The patient reports a maximum walking distance of 4 to 6 blocks.
The patient reports a maximum walking distance of 1 to 3 blocks.
The patient reports a walking distance of less than 1 block.
Patient-reported assessment of difficulty of walking on various surfaces.
No difficulty on any walking surface
The patient reports no difficulty walking on any surface.
The patient reports some difficulty walking on uneven terrains, stairs, inclines or ladders.
The patient reports severe difficulty walking on uneven terrains, stairs, inclines or ladders.
Patient-reported estimation of extent of pain on a scale of 0 to 100, where 0 indicates no pain and 100 indicates severe pain.
The subjective clinical history of the subject of care as recorded directly by the subject, or reported to a clinician by the subject or a carer.
Default, unspecified point in time or interval event which may be explicitly defined in a template or at run-time.
Narrative description of the story or clinical history for the subject of care.
Structured detail about the individual's story or patient's history.
For example: a specific symptom such as nausea or pain; an event such as a fall off a bicycle; or an issue such as a desire to quit using tobacco.
Additional information required to capture local content or to align with other reference models/formalisms.
For example: Local information requirements or additional metadata to align with FHIR or CIMI equivalents.
Document to communicate information to others, commonly in response to a request from another party.
The status of the entire report. Note: This is not the status of any of the report components.
Additional information required to capture local context or to align with other reference models/formalisms.
For example: local information requirements or additional metadata to align with FHIR or CIMI equivalents.
